# -------------------------------------------------------------------
# Git Commit Message Template
# -------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# Format:
# <type>(optional scope): <short summary>
#
# Examples:
# feat(auth): add JWT refresh token support
# fix(api): handle nil pointer in user handler
#
# -------------------------------------------------------------------
# TYPES:
# feat     → new feature
# fix      → bug fix
# refactor → code change that doesn’t add features or fix bugs
# chore    → tooling, build, CI, deps
# docs     → documentation only changes
# test     → adding or updating tests
# perf     → performance improvements
# style    → formatting, no logic change
# ci       → CI/CD changes
# build    → build system changes
# revert   → revert previous commit
# -------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# BODY (optional):
# Explain WHY this change is needed and WHAT changed.
#
# - bullet points are good
# - keep it focused and short
#
# Example:
#
# Why:
# - JWT tokens were expiring too early causing logout issues
#
# What:
# - increased token TTL
# - fixed refresh flow in auth middleware
#
# -------------------------------------------------------------------
# BREAKING CHANGES (if any):
# - describe breaking API / DB / behavior changes
#
# -------------------------------------------------------------------
# FOOTER (optional):
# Closes #123
# Fixes #456
#
# -------------------------------------------------------------------
